<dl id="s18007ak"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us18" href="#s18007ak">Penelope: </a><a href="../../ff/unbs/s18all.htm#s18007ak">sector 7(ak)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> LB couldn&apos;t adulter so gets BB to do it <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="s18007ak"><li>Ulysses </li><li><a href="../../ulex/t/lext.htm#s18007ak">2021</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/t/t86.htm#s18007ak">2017</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/t/t86.htm#s18007ak">1986 (18.1253f)</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/t/l22t.htm#s18007ak">1922</a> </li><li><ms href="#s18007ak">MS NLI.14-11</ms> </li><li><a name="t11d" href="../udra/u18da.htm#t11d">Usage</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/t/t11d.htm#s18007ak">Draft: 18.1</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><mark>Richard, unfitted for adulterous intercourse</mark> with the wives of his friends because it would involve a great deal of pretence on his part rather than because he is convinced of any dishonourableness in it, <mark>wishes, it seems, to feel the thrill of adultery vicariously</mark> and to possess a bound woman Bertha through the organ of his friend. <small> James Joyce, notes for <a name="JJEX" href="/udra/udex.htm#jjex"><cite title="source">Exiles</cite></a> (ca. 1913), p. 50f.</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
